from transformers import pipeline
summarizer=pipeline("summarization",model="facebook/bart-large-cnn")
long_text="""The Hugging Face Transformers library is a powerful open-source tool designed to make it easier for developers and researchers to use state-of-the-art natural language processing (NLP) models. It provides access to a wide variety of pre-trained models such as BERT, GPT, RoBERTa, T5, and many others that are built on the transformer architecture—a deep learning model designed to handle sequential data like text. These models are capable of performing a wide range of language-related tasks including text classification, question answering, translation, summarization, and text generation. What makes the Hugging Face Transformers library especially appealing is its ease of use and integration; with just a few lines of code, users can load a pre-trained model, tokenize text, and generate predictions. It also supports both PyTorch and TensorFlow, making it flexible for different deep learning frameworks. Additionally, the library is supported by a thriving community and comes with extensive documentation, tutorials, and examples, which help users quickly get started and experiment with cutting-edge NLP techniques. Hugging Face has also built the "Hub"—a platform where users can upload and share their own models and datasets, contributing to a more collaborative and open AI ecosystem."""
summary=summarizer(long_text,max_length=100,min_length=30,do_sample=False)
print("summary",summary[0]['summary_text'])
